## 10. Success Criteria

The implementation is successful when:

1. **Commutator correctly computed**: All four components (Δ_E, Δ_V, Δ_A, Δ_C) in [0, 1] range
2. **Dynamic hopping works**: Simple queries use 1-2 hops, complex queries use 4-6 hops
3. **Mode selection correct**: At least 6/8 test queries get expected mode
4. **Confidence calibrated**: Exploit mode > 0.7 confidence, Explore mode < 0.4 confidence
5. **Trajectory visible**: Clear convergence/divergence patterns in visualization
6. **Operator scores meaningful**: Higher score correlates with better evidence coverage

